      <p>Although we have seen how to create commit messages using conventional commits, it is quite possible that we might make mistakes, so we can use tools that guide us in the creation of these messages. We are going to look at two: <code>commitizen</code> and the <code>Conventional Commits</code> plugin for vscode.</p>
